HEADWORD: Tinto
<hw>Tin"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg., tinged, fr. L.
<ets>tinctus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>tingere</ets> to tinge. See
<er>Tint</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A red Madeira wine, wanting the
high aroma of the white sorts, and, when old, resembling tawny
port.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

